I am still Supremo of this school.

288
00:28:20,694 --> 00:28:24,114
I can choose who I protect.

289
00:28:25,949 --> 00:28:27,576
That's enough for now.

290
00:28:34,416 --> 00:28:35,751
But I also know

291
00:28:36,377 --> 00:28:38,253
that I can't protect everyone

292
00:28:39,046 --> 00:28:40,506
that I want to protect.

293
00:28:43,050 --> 00:28:44,843
I can take care of myself.

294
00:28:46,220 --> 00:28:47,220
Really?

295
00:28:51,141 --> 00:28:52,559
You don't believe me?

296
00:28:57,481 --> 00:28:59,400
That's not the Zein Shion I know.

297
00:29:00,776 --> 00:29:01,860
You ignored Matt.

298
00:29:03,570 --> 00:29:05,239
You looked away from him.

299
00:29:06,824 --> 00:29:07,991
That wasn't Zein.

300
00:29:09,410 --> 00:29:10,994
That wasn't my secretary.

301
00:29:13,163 --> 00:29:15,165
I'm still the same Zein Shion.

302
00:29:18,085 --> 00:29:20,045
The weak have no place here.

303
00:29:21,338 --> 00:29:23,257
They're nothing but garbage.

304
00:29:27,261 --> 00:29:28,887
The Zein Shion that I know

305
00:29:29,555 --> 00:29:31,890
loves her friends.

306
00:29:32,433 --> 00:29:34,685
That's why I looked up to her.

307
00:29:37,938 --> 00:29:39,898
If you really know me

308
00:29:41,150 --> 00:29:43,777
you should know
that I do taekwondo.

309
00:29:47,489 --> 00:29:49,408
So again, Supremo.

310
00:29:49,825 --> 00:29:51,743
I can take care of myself.

311
00:29:54,329 --> 00:29:55,747
I’ll be the judge of that.

312
00:29:56,623 --> 00:29:58,063
You have to show
me your moves first.

313
00:29:58,667 --> 00:29:59,793
Any time.

314
00:30:01,503 --> 00:30:03,005
SSG office.

315
00:30:03,922 --> 00:30:06,216
Anytime you're
free after last period.

316
00:30:07,384 --> 00:30:08,469
Brace yourself.

317
00:30:13,140 --> 00:30:14,725
Now that my secretary is back,

318
00:30:16,226 --> 00:30:17,561
she's ready to join me.

319
00:30:18,937 --> 00:30:20,063
To where, Supremo?

320
00:30:22,232 --> 00:30:23,232
To the admin.

321
00:30:23,859 --> 00:30:25,944
So we can truly save
Lyka and Ms. Aya.

322
00:30:52,596 --> 00:30:54,848
I'll handle Violet and Mr. Francisco.

323
00:31:35,055 --> 00:31:38,058
What a rare occurence,
Mr. President.

324
00:31:38,809 --> 00:31:40,185
What brings you here?

325
00:31:43,564 --> 00:31:44,982
I'll speak plainly

326
00:31:46,275 --> 00:31:48,986
exemption for Ms. Aya.

327
00:31:50,946 --> 00:31:52,030
Exemption?

328
00:31:54,866 --> 00:32:00,872
Mr. President, there are
rules and precedents to respect.

329
00:32:07,296 --> 00:32:10,257
But who am I to turn down a favor

330
00:32:10,424 --> 00:32:13,594
for my Supreme Student
Government President?

331
00:32:15,554 --> 00:32:17,055
But I'm just wondering

332
00:32:18,223 --> 00:32:20,225
what's the cause of this weakness?

333
00:32:26,148 --> 00:32:28,775
There are still limits, Madam.

334
00:32:29,985 --> 00:32:32,529
Even in a hell hole
like this university.

335
00:32:37,743 --> 00:32:41,705
I know that you're aware of the
consequences of this exemption.

336
00:32:42,456 --> 00:32:47,919
Mr. President, you must never
forget the only rule of your position.

337
00:32:50,672 --> 00:32:53,759
That you must never
get involved with anyone.

338
00:32:58,096 --> 00:33:00,057
You are not allowed
to make friends.

339
00:33:00,557 --> 00:33:04,436
Never let your emotions
hinder your path.

340
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:07,230
You don't have to worry about me.

341
00:33:09,066 --> 00:33:10,525
I know what I'm doing.

342
00:33:20,911 --> 00:33:22,579
I really do hope so.

343
00:33:23,914 --> 00:33:25,040
Okay then.

344
00:33:25,499 --> 00:33:27,709
I will give them the exemption.

345
00:33:29,544 --> 00:33:30,671
Tell them

346
00:33:31,129 --> 00:33:32,881
that they can breathe

347
00:33:35,133 --> 00:33:36,343
for now.

348
00:33:41,056 --> 00:33:43,308
You remind me of Lux.

349
00:33:44,101 --> 00:33:47,187
I'm nothing like him.

350
00:33:51,066 --> 00:33:53,276
The mother and child
is safe for now.

351
00:33:54,236 --> 00:33:55,612
But you

352
00:34:04,788 --> 00:34:06,164
you're safe too.

353
00:34:07,207 --> 00:34:08,333
Impressive.

354
00:34:09,126 --> 00:34:10,127
Me?

355
00:34:11,253 --> 00:34:13,505
The one who picked
your name is dead.

356
00:34:15,340 --> 00:34:17,509
I guess you have a
guardian angel, Ms. Shion.

357
00:34:26,143 --> 00:34:27,561
Where did you
pick up that stray?

358
00:34:29,730 --> 00:34:32,607
He followed me, ma'am.

359
00:34:35,068 --> 00:34:36,695
I'll set him free later.

360
00:34:37,696 --> 00:34:39,865
Make sure to do it soon.

361
00:34:43,827 --> 00:34:45,120
Are we done here?

362
00:34:46,663 --> 00:34:49,082
For now, Madam.

363
00:35:18,153 --> 00:35:20,257
Attention, students.

364
00:35:20,282 --> 00:35:22,993
The locker game is now concluded.

365
00:35:25,535 --> 00:35:28,205
Any pending business is void.

366
00:35:28,872 --> 00:35:31,792
Carry on with your remaining classes.

367
00:35:38,757 --> 00:35:42,052
It's done for now.

368
00:35:43,512 --> 00:35:45,472
This isn't peace.

369
00:36:13,124 --> 00:36:15,627
Do you have any
suggestions, Ms. Shion?

370
00:36:18,213 --> 00:36:19,213
Huh?

371
00:36:21,424 --> 00:36:23,260
Are you with us, Ms. Shion?

372
00:36:24,928 --> 00:36:26,763
You're supposed to be
the one planning this.

373
00:36:27,597 --> 00:36:29,349
You're the secretary.

374
00:36:29,516 --> 00:36:32,310
We are just here to
approve your suggestions.

375
00:36:35,689 --> 00:36:40,235
I guess leisure activities
and games should be fun.

376
00:36:41,736 --> 00:36:42,946
That's your idea?

377
00:36:46,491 --> 00:36:47,534
Then write it.

378
00:37:26,531 --> 00:37:27,824
I must say.

379
00:37:30,619 --> 00:37:32,287
This is a brilliant idea.

380
00:37:39,210 --> 00:37:41,212
If there are no objections to this list...

381
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:48,053
then I approve.

382
00:37:57,896 --> 00:37:59,022
I keep telling you all

383
00:37:59,814 --> 00:38:02,025
she's more than
qualified for this position.

384
00:38:04,361 --> 00:38:07,280
If there isn't anything else

385
00:38:07,489 --> 00:38:09,157
may I ask to take my leave?

386
00:38:09,741 --> 00:38:11,618
I think we have what
we need, Ms. Shion.

387
00:38:11,993 --> 00:38:12,993
You may go.

388
00:38:45,652 --> 00:38:47,320
A penny for your thoughts?

389
00:38:52,325 --> 00:38:56,162
Everything is so complicated.

390
00:39:01,459 --> 00:39:05,714
And we tend to overcomplicate it more.

391
00:39:08,842 --> 00:39:10,260
What the fuck do you want?

392
00:39:11,678 --> 00:39:12,887
I'm busy.

393
00:39:13,555 --> 00:39:15,181
Whoa, harsh!

394
00:39:15,557 --> 00:39:18,351
Well, I was just...

395
00:39:18,935 --> 00:39:21,021
wondering about a few things and

396
00:39:21,396 --> 00:39:22,897
maybe you can help me out.

397
00:39:27,152 --> 00:39:32,323
Why do feelings suddenly change?

398
00:39:40,290 --> 00:39:41,708
What are you trying to say?

399
00:39:42,751 --> 00:39:43,209
I'm sorry

400
00:39:43,210 --> 00:39:44,419
what I mean is

401
00:39:44,919 --> 00:39:49,716
why do people change?

402
00:39:52,802 --> 00:39:55,889
Because there's nothing
permanent in this world.

403
00:39:57,640 --> 00:39:59,767
If you're done asking
nonsensical questions

404
00:39:59,768 --> 00:40:01,102
you can leave.

405
00:40:05,732 --> 00:40:07,942
Even with friends?

406
00:40:14,365 --> 00:40:15,700
Nothing is permanent.

407
00:40:16,284 --> 00:40:17,660
I'll take note of that.

408
00:40:18,328 --> 00:40:19,204
By the way

409
00:40:19,205 --> 00:40:21,998
thank you for your answers, Zein.

410
00:40:55,698 --> 00:40:56,698
Ms. Shion.

411
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:00,160
Damn it!

412
00:41:00,411 --> 00:41:01,411
Ms. Shion

413
00:41:01,663 --> 00:41:03,373
get this little shit off of me!

414
00:41:04,415 --> 00:41:06,835
Are you... afraid of cats?

415
00:41:14,676 --> 00:41:17,053
You are afraid of cats!

416
00:41:19,639 --> 00:41:20,639
Ms. Shion!

417
00:41:24,561 --> 00:41:27,021
Are you not afraid of cats?

418
00:41:28,815 --> 00:41:30,108
I'm not afraid of them.

419
00:41:31,276 --> 00:41:32,276
I just...

420
00:41:33,236 --> 00:41:34,988
hate cats.

421
00:41:36,781 --> 00:41:38,825
There's nothing to hate about cats.

422
00:41:39,826 --> 00:41:41,286
You're just afraid of them.

423
00:41:42,453 --> 00:41:43,496
Ms. Shion,

424
00:41:44,080 --> 00:41:45,290
get him away from me.

425
00:41:50,420 --> 00:41:52,297
You know just admit it

426
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:54,757
you're just afraid of him.

427
00:41:56,426 --> 00:41:57,927
I am Ace Craige.

428
00:41:58,761 --> 00:42:00,180
I am afraid of no one.

429
00:42:02,348 --> 00:42:04,142
Especially not a

430
00:42:05,143 --> 00:42:06,143
cat.

431
00:42:06,561 --> 00:42:07,729
Really?

432
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:10,189
Daddy Ace.

433
00:42:10,190 --> 00:42:12,901
Baby Hoy wants to be carried.

434
00:42:13,610 --> 00:42:15,445
Carry me.

435
00:42:22,368 --> 00:42:24,704
Okay. I get it.

436
00:42:25,288 --> 00:42:26,873
You're not afraid of cats.

437
00:42:27,624 --> 00:42:29,000
Really?

438
00:42:30,543 --> 00:42:31,794
But

439
00:42:33,087 --> 00:42:34,631
are you afraid of me?

440
00:42:36,382 --> 00:42:37,425
What are you.

441
00:42:40,386 --> 00:42:41,429
Ouch!

442
00:42:43,056 --> 00:42:44,056
Ouch?

443
00:42:45,266 --> 00:42:46,643
Stop pinching, Zein!

444
00:42:47,018 --> 00:42:49,145
Dammit, that hurts!

445
00:42:59,864 --> 00:43:01,866
What the fuck is it now?

446
00:43:07,080 --> 00:43:09,916
You know... just a little more.

447
00:43:11,292 --> 00:43:14,420
It's not bad to smile
from time to time.

448
00:43:15,380 --> 00:43:17,173
You're not worth smiling about.

449
00:43:18,007 --> 00:43:21,302
Because I'm worth more
than you can imagine.

450
00:43:23,304 --> 00:43:24,304
Right?

451
00:43:24,931 --> 00:43:25,931
Smile!

452
00:43:26,849 --> 00:43:27,642
Never.

453
00:43:27,643 --> 00:43:28,935
Smile...

454
00:43:29,727 --> 00:43:30,895
He's telling you to smile.

455
00:43:34,190 --> 00:43:35,190
Smile!

456
00:43:36,401 --> 00:43:37,610
Never!

457
00:43:37,944 --> 00:43:39,195
You don't want to?

458
00:43:41,572 --> 00:43:42,824
Wasn’t I clear?

459
00:43:44,951 --> 00:43:45,951
Smile!

460
00:43:47,537 --> 00:43:48,788
You really won't do it?

461
00:43:50,331 --> 00:43:51,541
Are you content?

462
00:43:53,084 --> 00:43:53,876
Look at you, oh!

463
00:43:53,877 --> 00:43:55,128
You're smiling!

464
00:43:55,461 --> 00:43:56,671
I'm going to count.

465
00:43:58,006 --> 00:43:59,006
One...

466
00:43:59,173 --> 00:44:00,300
Sorry...

467
00:44:01,259 --> 00:44:02,259
Two...

468
00:44:02,510 --> 00:44:04,386
I was just... you knew
I was just kidding!

469
00:44:04,387 --> 00:44:05,430
Three.

470
00:44:16,441 --> 00:44:17,441
Ouch!

471
00:44:21,863 --> 00:44:22,905
Are you ready?

472
00:44:29,620 --> 00:44:31,372
If you're talking about my death.

473
00:44:33,291 --> 00:44:34,417
Always.

474
00:44:36,669 --> 00:44:37,669
You sure?

475
00:44:39,297 --> 00:44:40,965
You still got a couple days left.

476
00:44:43,634 --> 00:44:44,635
Aren't you...

477
00:44:46,554 --> 00:44:48,598
Aren't you going to
ask for my help again?

478
00:44:53,311 --> 00:44:55,146
You can't do anything about it.

479
00:44:57,940 --> 00:45:00,026
Is that really how you see me?

480
00:45:09,243 --> 00:45:10,536
You must know.

481
00:45:12,830 --> 00:45:14,457
I am not named Ace

482
00:45:15,291 --> 00:45:16,584
without one.

483
00:45:19,962 --> 00:45:21,130
Think about it.

484
00:45:42,485 --> 00:45:43,528
Ew!

485
00:45:48,116 --> 00:45:49,158
Van!

486
00:45:49,492 --> 00:45:50,368
Get out!

487
00:45:50,369 --> 00:45:51,910
OMG Van!

488
00:45:51,911 --> 00:45:52,620
What?

489
00:45:52,621 --> 00:45:53,788
What are you doing!?

490
00:45:54,038 --> 00:45:56,416
Stop it, that's animal abuse!

491
00:45:56,958 --> 00:45:57,958
You poor baby.

492
00:45:57,959 --> 00:45:58,959
- What animal abuse?
- Zein!

493
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:00,002
Stay away from it, Zein.

494
00:46:00,294 --> 00:46:01,754
Are you okay, Hoy?

495
00:46:01,963 --> 00:46:03,713
You poor thing.

496
00:46:03,714 --> 00:46:04,465
Poor baby.

497
00:46:04,466 --> 00:46:05,549
Zein!

498
00:46:05,550 --> 00:46:07,175
What are you doing?

499
00:46:07,176 --> 00:46:08,552
Stay away from that!

500
00:46:08,553 --> 00:46:09,928
That's a ghost!

501
00:46:09,929 --> 00:46:10,847
A ghost?

502
00:46:10,848 --> 00:46:12,097
This cute cat?

503
00:46:12,098 --> 00:46:14,057
His name is Hoy.

504
00:46:14,058 --> 00:46:15,058
Poor baby.

505
00:46:15,059 --> 00:46:15,810
Hoy?

506
00:46:15,811 --> 00:46:17,519
Were you scared?

507
00:46:17,520 --> 00:46:19,897
He's traumatized because
of the two of you.

508
00:46:20,481 --> 00:46:21,524
Hey!

509
00:46:21,816 --> 00:46:23,275
You were the one who hit it.

510
00:46:23,276 --> 00:46:24,818
Poor baby.

511
00:46:24,819 --> 00:46:26,153
You're too naughty.

512
00:46:26,154 --> 00:46:27,905
That's just a friendly pat!

513
00:46:28,531 --> 00:46:30,157
You're such a naughty baby.

514
00:46:30,158 --> 00:46:31,784
Look where it got you.

515
00:46:32,660 --> 00:46:33,660
Here you go.

516
00:46:37,999 --> 00:46:39,417
Have you seen Matt?

517
00:46:41,377 --> 00:46:42,670
Did you guys fight?

518
00:46:43,045 --> 00:46:44,922
Why did it get weird
between the two of you?

519
00:46:46,215 --> 00:46:47,215
It's nothing.

520
00:46:47,717 --> 00:46:48,259
Really?

521
00:46:48,260 --> 00:46:49,385
Nothing happened?

522
00:46:49,677 --> 00:46:51,512
Why are you guys
avoiding each other?

523
00:46:55,016 --> 00:46:56,016
Because.

524
00:47:06,819 --> 00:47:07,819
We need to talk.

525
00:47:11,073 --> 00:47:13,201
We have nothing to talk about.

526
00:47:13,951 --> 00:47:16,912
My body is suddenly aching, Mia.

527
00:47:16,913 --> 00:47:17,705
Can you give me a massage?

528
00:47:17,706 --> 00:47:18,748
Come on, let's go.

529
00:47:31,010 --> 00:47:32,010
Sorry.

530
00:47:35,431 --> 00:47:37,266
I'm too good at this.

531
00:47:37,725 --> 00:47:41,103
- I made you believe I was upset with you.
- Sorry if I...

532
00:47:42,647 --> 00:47:44,482
seemed cold towards you

533
00:47:45,274 --> 00:47:46,901
these past days.

534
00:47:48,903 --> 00:47:51,030
My mind has been
overloaded with things.

535
00:47:53,741 --> 00:47:55,826
You don't need to say sorry, Zein.

536
00:47:59,622 --> 00:48:02,542
I wouldn't care even if
you were avoiding me.

537
00:48:03,501 --> 00:48:04,919
I'll always try to understand you.

538
00:48:06,379 --> 00:48:09,048
You don't need to
apologize for anything.

539
00:48:09,757 --> 00:48:11,092
You didn't do anything bad.

540
00:48:11,425 --> 00:48:16,180
Apologies are for those
who did something bad.

541
00:48:22,562 --> 00:48:24,480
I hate myself.

542
00:48:27,275 --> 00:48:29,026
I'm so frustrated with myself.

543
00:48:33,364 --> 00:48:35,074
A lot has happened

544
00:48:35,658 --> 00:48:36,409
and then-

545
00:48:36,410 --> 00:48:38,160
Shhh.

546
00:48:42,498 --> 00:48:43,749
It's nothing.

547
00:48:44,584 --> 00:48:47,628
I'm sorry if I made you feel that way.

548
00:48:54,552 --> 00:48:55,636
That hurts.

549
00:48:58,014 --> 00:48:59,223
I hate you!

550
00:49:04,770 --> 00:49:07,231
I hate you because.

551
00:49:10,067 --> 00:49:14,530
I can't trust you the way
you obviously trust me.

552
00:49:18,909 --> 00:49:20,995
I know you have a reason, Zein.

553
00:49:22,121 --> 00:49:23,997
I won't force you to tell me

554
00:49:23,998 --> 00:49:27,126
the reason why you became
cold towards me...

555
00:49:27,335 --> 00:49:29,128
why you started avoiding me.

556
00:49:30,338 --> 00:49:32,423
Because I don't care
about that anyway.

557
00:49:34,133 --> 00:49:35,968
What's important to me is

558
00:49:37,595 --> 00:49:39,847
my belief that in the end

559
00:49:40,806 --> 00:49:42,683
I'll still be the one
you'll embrace.

560
00:49:46,979 --> 00:49:48,147
Come here.

561
00:49:56,280 --> 00:49:57,615
Maybe, I was wrong

562
00:49:58,991 --> 00:50:00,701
but it is never too late.

563
00:50:01,702 --> 00:50:03,245
Whatever your reason may be.

564
00:50:04,163 --> 00:50:06,874
I’ll trust you, Matthew Hart.

565
00:50:20,888 --> 00:50:21,681
Ladies and gentlemen

566
00:50:21,682 --> 00:50:22,682
welcome to.

567
00:50:22,973 --> 00:50:24,224
Hell University's

568
00:50:24,225 --> 00:50:27,019
Mr. and Ms. Face of the Year!

569
00:50:31,649 --> 00:50:34,943
See? We didn't make a
mistake by choosing Matt

570
00:50:34,944 --> 00:50:37,988
as our class representative.

571
00:50:42,410 --> 00:50:43,953
Matt! Go, Matt!

